gm-method: when auditing a 'all key reads route through keyring/single-source' invariant, a grep for process.env.<PROVIDER>_API_KEY must be CLASSIFIED not counted — distinguish (a) presence-checks 'if(process.env.X)' that only boolean-gate and are safe, (b) the keyring's own internal reads (the sanctioned source), (c) genuine VALUE-reads 'apiKey || process.env.X' used as the live request credential that bypass rotation/backoff. A prior memo claiming 'only 3 direct reads' undercounted because it missed category (c) value-reads in provider modules and a discovery path. The witness is Read of each grep site, not the grep count.